    {
      "id": "CVE-2024-4867",
      "publishedDate": "2026-04-16T09:32:40.941Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-04-16T12:30:42.568Z",
      "description": "The WSO2 API Manager developer portal accepts user-supplied input without enforcing expected validation constraints or proper output encoding. This deficiency allows a malicious actor to inject script content that is executed within the context of a user's browser.\n\nBy leveraging this cross-site scripting vulnerability, a malicious actor can cause the browser to redirect to a malicious website, make changes to the UI of the web page, or retrieve information from the browser. However, session hijacking is not possible as all session-related sensitive cookies are protected by the httpOnly flag.",
      "severity": 5.4,
      "references": [
